place.name: STRIXTON
place.gazetteerText: STRIXTON, a parish in Wellingborough district, Northampton; 4 miles S by W of Wellingborough r. station. Post town, Wellingborough. Acres, 889. Real property, £1,237. Pop., 61. Houses, 12. The living is a rectory, annexed to Bozeat, in the diocese of Peterborough. The church is early English. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
